(2) On the hearing of an application under paragraph (a) of subsection (1) , the Disciplinary Committee may recommend to the Chief Justice that the name of such practitioner be removed from the Roll , and, upon such recommendation, the Chief Justice may order that the name be removed or make such other order in relation to the case as he may think fit.
